    "updated_at": "2014-08-28T01:51:30Z",
    "body": "Forking at all with the standard library has completely undefined behaviour. There are bigger problems than the task-local RNG so I don't really think it can be considered a bug in isolation. Rust's standard library isn't really a library, it's a managed framework that runs your code and you have to obey certain rules.\n\nSee #9568\n",
