    "created_at": "2014-09-06T15:51:38Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-09-06T15:55:20Z",
    "body": "Forking with the runtime is known to be unsupported. There are dozens of reasons why it is broken / completely memory unsafe. If you want it to be supported, then file an RFC about supporting it as a whole. You'll need to come up with a clear design for making it work properly. An individual problem resulting from the choice not to support `fork` isn't a bug. I closed the earlier bug I filed because I didn't have any realistic answers to @brson's question about how we can actually make this safe as a whole.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
