    "created_at": "2016-01-13T06:12:32Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-01-13T06:12:32Z",
    "body": "I agree that this isn't an issue for HashMap itself (or rather, it's not a problem for SipHash), but the original CVE's cited were for reseeding OpenSSL's entropy pool (for generating private keys, presumably).\n\nThat said: Rust doesn't have official RNG anymore. It's all in the `rand` library. As far as I can tell, nothing has changed and your argument that OsRng should be robust to forks should hold. Presumably, any security library would use that.\n",
